# Agentic Delivery Workflow

Before coding in this repository, read:

- `AGENTS.workflow.md`
- `.agentic-workflow.yml`
- `docs/wp/RULINGS.md`

Follow the lane decision before editing files:

- Program/Migration: audit first, freeze `docs/wp/program-manifest.md`, sequence by risk, gate every wave, and require backup/dry-run/approval for irreversible work.
- Work Package: branch first, story/progress files, scoped implementation, verification.
- Small Fix: only tiny low-risk changes within the configured limits.
- Gate: verification only; report failures and assign scoped fixes.

Worktrees are allowed only under `.worktrees/`. Never create sibling project folders for work packages.

Use one agent by default. Use sub-agents only for parallel work packages, independent review, gate runs, or context isolation. Route stronger models to orchestration, architecture, security/auth/payments/publishing, production data, migrations, AI/prompt behavior, and final review; use cheaper models for scaffolding, inventories, docs cleanup, running checks, and mechanical lint fixes.
